nergy transport out of the jet cone of\n$2.8\\pm0.2\\mathrm{(stat)}\\pm1.5\\mathrm{(sys)}$ GeV/c, for\n$10<p_T^\\mathrm{jet,ch}<20$ GeV/c and R = 0.5. No medium-induced change in jet\nshape is observed for $R<0.5$. The azimuthal distribution of\nlow-$p_T^\\mathrm{jet,ch}$ recoil jets may be enhanced at large azimuthal angles\nto the trigger axis, due to scattering off quasi-particles in the hot QCD\nmedium. Measurement of this distribution gives a 90% statistical confidence\nupper limit to the yield enhancement at large deflection angles in central\nAu+Au collisions of $50\\pm30\\mathrm{(sys)\\%}$ of the large-angle yield in\np+pcollisions predicted by PYTHIA.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Fri, 3 Feb 2017 18:40:08 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-23"}
